INUMBER 1916
NAME 316
ARMOR
WORN_BODY
OPENABLE
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 20
WEIGHT 10
VOLUME 5
*DESCRIPTION_START EXAMINE
Thin silvery threads have been intricately hand-woven together to form
this full length robe. Intricate designs of Drakin artistry have been
sewn into the robe with meticulous care so that it appears as if the
designs shimmer with each movement of the wearer. Sewn onto the back
of the robe are the following words;

                      "Duea'Ktrang Ntigoth"
                          "Sass'reate"
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
  IFITEM -1 WORN
    IFVAR INTNUM47 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
    ENDIF
     IFVAR INTNUM47 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "In my time I was known as one of the mighty amongst my clan."
     ENDIF
     IFVAR INTNUM47 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "In my time I was known as one of the mighty amongst my clan."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice intones, "My house is Edroha, honor it well. Master of both within my clan, neither art closed to me. Name me, Kih'tha'nohg, for such did the revered ancestors call me on the night of my birthing. It means, Walker amongst the Lights.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR INTNUM47 = 4
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "In my time I was known as one of the mighty amongst my clan."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice intones, "My house is Edroha, honor it well. Master of both within my clan, neither art closed to me. Name me, Kih'tha'nohg, for such did the revered ancestors call me on the night of my birthing. It means, Walker amongst the Lights.
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "Bearer and Creator of the Mind Sai was I. Many Jupaaskri fell before my might, curse them and all their foul spawn."
     ENDIF
     IFVAR INTNUM47 = 5
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "In my time I was known as one of the mighty amongst my clan."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice intones, "My house is Edroha, honor it well. Master of both within my clan, neither art closed to me. Name me, Kih'tha'nohg, for such did the revered ancestors call me on the night of my birthing. It means, Walker amongst the Lights.
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "Bearer and Creator of the Mind Sai was I. Many Jupaaskri fell before my might, curse them and all their foul spawn."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "My name struck fear within Jupaaskri souls, deep into their warrens I went, using the power of Pi'tho'norksa to stay their poisons."
     ENDIF
     IFVAR INTNUM47 = 6
      ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "I am of the clan Sass'reate, Kvaahn Cho'Nya."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "In my time I was known as one of the mighty amongst my clan."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice intones, "My house is Edroha, honor it well. Master of both within my clan, neither art closed to me. Name me, Kih'tha'nohg, for such did the revered ancestors call me on the night of my birthing. It means, Walker amongst the Lights.
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "Bearer and Creator of the Mind Sai was I. Many Jupaaskri fell before my might, curse them and all their foul spawn."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "My name struck fear within Jupaaskri souls, deep into their warrens I went, using the power of Pi'tho'norksa to stay their poisons."
      ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "Pi'tho'norksa, the Essence of the Stars, inhaled before my ancestors, with their blessings. A magical mixture whose secret died with me. Without it, journey into the Jupaaskri home will make all drakin fall."
     ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
  CLEARVERB
    IFITEM -1 WORN
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 1
        ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "The robe I am, and the robe is me. Mysteries to unlock for its wearer. Part by part, thread by thread, discover the past and find the future."
        ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "Unravel the first, listen to my clue...In the ruined ground, thrusting towards to the sky, all the races to be found."
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 2
        ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "The robe I am, and the robe is me. Mysteries to unlock for its wearer. Part by part, thread by thread, discover the past and find the future."
        ECHO PLAYER The voice speaks softly within your mind, "On to the second, now is the time to be reckoned....The four wolves snarl from the corners, even their great hunger dwarfed by the cruelty of the darkness."
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 3
        ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "The robe I am, and the robe is me. Mysteries to unlock for its wearer. Part by part, thread by thread, discover the past and find the future."
        ECHO PLAYER The voice continues, "This task is three in number, listen closely lest you blunder.....Humming fills your ears, Heat nearly more than you can bear, From the tree that is not a tree."
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 4
        ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "The robe I am, and the robe is me. Mysteries to unlock for its wearer. Part by part, thread by thread, discover the past and find the future."
        ECHO PLAYER The voice fills your mind, "Three doors unlocked, the fourth has now beckoned.....Jaws of stone threaten, a reddish light flowing from teeth that are not together."
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 5
        ECHO PLAYER A gentle voice speaks within your mind, "The robe I am, and the robe is me. Mysteries to unlock for its wearer. Part by part, thread by thread, discover the past and find the future."
        ECHO PLAYER The voice nearly roars in your mind, "The star almost completed, let this fifth clue not be repeated...The water splits the cavern of one who called it home so long ago, only tools remain, no more use due to time's abuse"
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
  CLEARVERB
    IFITEM -1 WORN
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 1
       IFVAR RNUM = 506
         ECHO PLAYER As you pull at the robe you hear a relieved sigh within your mind and then you see a silvery thread float to the ground from the cloak. The voice speaks, "Only the first unravelled, more to come, patience will see us through."
         ECHO OTHERS %N gently pulls at %h robe and you see a single silver thread fall to the ground.
         NEWITEM 9 1970 ADJ1=292
         EQUAL INTNUM47 2
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 2
       IFVAR RNUM = 1332
         ECHO PLAYER As you pull at the robe you hear a relieved sigh within your mind and then you see a silvery thread float to the ground from the cloak. The voice speaks, "Only the first unravelled, more to come, patience will see us through."
         ECHO OTHERS %N gently pulls at %h robe and you see a single silver thread fall to the ground.
         NEWITEM 9 1970 ADJ1=292
         EQUAL INTNUM47 3
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 3
       IFVAR RNUM = 1156
         ECHO PLAYER As you pull at the robe you hear a relieved sigh within your mind and then you see a silvery thread float to the ground from the cloak. The voice speaks, "Only the first unravelled, more to come, patience will see us through."
         ECHO OTHERS %N gently pulls at %h robe and you see a single silver thread fall to the ground.
         NEWITEM 9 1970 ADJ1=292
         EQUAL INTNUM47 4
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 4
       IFVAR RNUM = 959
         ECHO PLAYER As you pull at the robe you hear a relieved sigh within your mind and then you see a silvery thread float to the ground from the cloak. The voice speaks, "Only the first unravelled, more to come, patience will see us through."
         ECHO OTHERS %N gently pulls at %h robe and you see a single silver thread fall to the ground.
         NEWITEM 9 1970 ADJ1=292
         EQUAL INTNUM47 5
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM47 = 5
       IFVAR RNUM = 725
         ECHO PLAYER As you pull at the robe you hear a relieved sigh within your mind and then you see a silvery thread float to the ground from the cloak. The voice speaks, "Only the first unravelled, more to come, patience will see us through."
         ECHO OTHERS %N gently pulls at %h robe and you see a single silver thread fall to the ground.
         NEWITEM 9 1970 ADJ1=292
         EQUAL INTNUM47 6
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
