INUMBER 1884
NAME 167
WORN_RING
ARMOR
IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 612
  IFPREVERB LOOK -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The diamonds and moonstones offset each other, bright white and cool grey. The band is a conglomerate of silver and veins of old iron, bound around a core of unbreakable alzyron.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB READ -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER An inscription reads, "Mine. Yours. Ours. Us."
  ENDIF
  IFVERB RECALL -1
    IFVAR INTNUM3 = 78
      ECHO PLAYER You remember the overwhelming wave of love washing over you as the truths were spoken, the sense of completeness that it gave you... and the bond is forged in you all over again.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR INTNUM3 = 21
      ECHO PLAYER In the farthest reaches of your mind, you recall giving this ring to Camorra.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
