; illithium mesh armor
INUMBER 306
NAME 8
VOLUME 8
WEIGHT 10
ARTICLE SOME
WORN_ARMOR
ARMOR
ENCRUSTABLE
PARAMETER1 75
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
IFVAR ITEMVAL2 > 15
  IFPREVERB WEAR -1
    RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
    IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
      EQUAL DUMMY1 0
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The mesh of illithium frays slightly.
      SUB ITEMVAL2 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER GM: Illithium armor, non-unique. When worn and val2>15, there a is 1 in 3 chance that the material will fray an the val2 will decrease. This is overridden if itembit0=1.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
; Reisthfaer's Armor
;
INUMBER 1848
NAME 8
WEIGHT 75
VOLUME 7
ARMOR
WORN_ARMOR
ARTICLE SOME
PARAMETER1 85
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER This armor has been carefully constructed from overlapping plates of just about every kind of metal imaginable. The most remarkable thing is the way the colors of the metal blend into on another, with subtle changes in hue.
  ECHO PLAYER Every single plate also seems to hold a faint reddish hue, as if it has absorbed a dye of some kind. The final grace of the armor is the intricate carvings of a blind mans face, staring out from the center of the plates, beckoning.
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER * - This is the archetype for Reisthfaer's armor - do not use - *
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
  IFITEM -1 WORN
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! TIM
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You concentrate on the symbol within your armor. Moments later you feel a strange trickling sensation, akin to blood running down your chest. It then occurs to you that your bleeding has stopped.
      ECHO OTHERS %N seems to have entered a state of supreme concentration as %s stares down at %h armor.
      SPELL 342 50
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 TIM
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The power of the armor, and the blood which flows through it cannot aid you at the moment.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You must be wearing the armor to invoke its powers.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You gaze down at your armor almost lovingly, and begin to steadily polish it.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gazes down at %h armor with almost a loving care, and begins to slowly polish it.
ENDIF
;